Wash and dry produce. Trim @green beans{6%ounce}. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Drizzle @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a hot pan. Add green beans, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and tender, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> While green beans cook, you can start prepping the salad in Step 3.

Turn off heat; transfer green beans to a #plate{}. (TIP: Cover with #foil{} to keep warm.) Wipe out pan.

Rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water; pat dry with #paper towels{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for green beans. Add shrimp; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until opaque and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @smoky garlic herb sauce{1%ounce} until warmed through, ~{30-60%seconds}.

In a #bowl{}, toss @mixed greens{4%ounce}, @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}, and @shredded carrots{4%ounce} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, juice from two lemon wedges (four wedges for 4), and as much @Greek vinaigrette{1.5%ounce} as you like.

Divide shrimp, salad, and green beans between plates. Top green beans with @crispy fried onions{1%unit}.

Garnish salad with @croutons{1%unit} (crush croutons in the bag with your hands right before serving). Serve with remaining lemon wedges.

> Shrimp is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.